Held over from 2020 due to the coronavirus pandemic, the European championships are due to be held in 12 different countries from June 11-July 11, with London's Wembley hosting the semis and final.Yet Uefa has warned it could change the venues if a host city insists on holding a match behind closed doors. Berlin, Germany 

Plans by European football's governing body Uefa to ensure fans can attend all fixtures at this year's delayed pan-continental Euros has sparked fury in Germany, where Munich is due to host matches. 

Held over from 2020 due to the coronavirus pandemic, the European championships are due to be held in 12 different countries from June 11-July 11, with London's Wembley hosting the semis and final. 



