Reiter also took a dig at European football's governing body. 

"Especially in these times, I would like to see those responsible at Uefa seek a direct exchange with the host cities in order to work out a solution together," he added. 

However, Uefa says the multi-venue format, whilst complex, gives organisers flexibility to deal with issues arising from the pandemic. 

"If we can no longer do anything in one country there are still 11 others where preparations are already in progress," Uefa's health advisor Daniel Koch told AFP at the start of the month. Nine candidates are fighting to replace Boniface Kabaka who died last year. Ex-Epra boss Pavel Oimeke resigned last week from to venture into politics. Andayi says it was unfortunate that the NLC official died under mysterious circumstances.